WEBVTT

00:04.091 --> 00:06.049
♪

00:10.532 --> 00:12.490
[exhales]

00:27.114 --> 00:29.551
[gasps][phone rings]

00:31.553 --> 00:33.555
Nancy, are you all right?

00:35.992 --> 00:37.950
Yeah.

00:37.994 --> 00:40.562
Sorry. I'm just
really tired.

00:40.605 --> 00:42.694
Well, if you weren't,
I'd be worried.

00:42.738 --> 00:45.306
You came face-to-face
with a serial killer yesterday,

00:45.349 --> 00:47.917
and you've been here all night
giving a statement.

00:47.960 --> 00:50.572
They said that you
wanted to talk to me.I can't stop thinking

00:50.615 --> 00:52.791
about the last thing
Trott said to me.

00:52.835 --> 00:55.577
I'm a part of
something much bigger.

00:55.620 --> 00:58.493
You'll never understand.

00:58.536 --> 01:00.321
"I'm a part
of something much bigger."

01:00.364 --> 01:01.757
I mean,
that has to mean something.

01:01.800 --> 01:03.063
Don't let him
get into your head.

01:03.106 --> 01:05.674
You put a killer behind bars.

01:05.717 --> 01:08.198
You did something extraordinary.

01:09.243 --> 01:11.158
Okay.

01:14.422 --> 01:16.119
Hey, I, um...

01:16.163 --> 01:19.905
Uh, I was hoping to-to check in
with Agent Park?

01:19.949 --> 01:23.300
Oh, uh, he's still in Portland
doing the transfer paperwork.Oh.

01:23.344 --> 01:25.694
Um... Thank you.

01:25.737 --> 01:27.435
[chuckles softly]

01:27.478 --> 01:30.046
Yes, it is a problem.
A big problem.

01:30.090 --> 01:31.526
Look at this.

01:31.569 --> 01:34.311
How are my customers
supposed to eat at that table

01:34.355 --> 01:35.747
with a bike there?

01:35.791 --> 01:37.184
It's an eyesore,

01:37.227 --> 01:39.099
and it's costing me money
every minute.

01:39.142 --> 01:42.102
And I know
it has something to do

01:42.145 --> 01:44.800
with that youth whatever
across the street.

01:44.843 --> 01:46.410
I know the owner of
the Youth Center.

01:46.454 --> 01:49.674
And as the community liaison,
I can talk to him

01:49.718 --> 01:51.676
about giving your café
a little more...

01:51.720 --> 01:52.938
Respect?

01:52.982 --> 01:54.940
Space.

01:54.984 --> 01:58.205
And don't forget to talk to him
about the loitering, as well.

01:58.248 --> 01:59.641
Yep. Got it.Thank you.

01:59.684 --> 02:02.296
I'm on it.
I'll see you later.Great.

02:04.559 --> 02:08.302
RYAN:
Oh, whee! Something
smells amazing.

02:08.345 --> 02:10.130
Ah, ah, ah, ah.

02:10.173 --> 02:12.828
I have a working lunch.A working lunch

02:12.871 --> 02:16.179
that, what, requires your
famous pasta primavera?Yes. Uh-huh.

02:16.223 --> 02:17.789
Wait.[sniffs]What are...?

02:17.833 --> 02:20.923
Are you... Are you
wearing aftershave?

02:21.967 --> 02:23.447
Okay.

02:23.491 --> 02:25.928
Okay, what exactly
are you working on?

02:25.971 --> 02:29.149
You should be working
on the chore wheel.

02:29.192 --> 02:30.889
I believe you
have trash duty.

02:30.933 --> 02:33.979
Uh, floors,
and they're swept. Check it.

02:34.023 --> 02:35.546
Now you can tell Nancy
that I'm getting better

02:35.590 --> 02:36.852
at what she assigned me.

02:36.895 --> 02:40.464
Actually,
how about you tell her yourself

02:40.508 --> 02:42.640
over at the Youth Center.
It's the grand opening.

02:42.684 --> 02:44.033
Go support Nick,

02:44.076 --> 02:47.210
and then you and Nancy
can come back at 2:00 p.m.

02:47.254 --> 02:49.212
or anytime after 2:00.

02:49.256 --> 02:51.258
[doorbell rings]

02:56.001 --> 02:57.742
Hello.

02:57.786 --> 02:59.179
Hello.

03:01.311 --> 03:03.270
Working lunch? Yeah.

03:06.098 --> 03:08.057
Come in. Please.[chuckles]:Okay.

03:08.100 --> 03:09.754
♪ This round,
I'm taking my time ♪

03:09.798 --> 03:12.453
♪ Taking my time,
taking my time, yeah ♪

03:12.496 --> 03:14.324
♪ Take charge, yeah,
I'm repping my style ♪

03:14.368 --> 03:16.892
♪ Repping my style,
repping my style, yeah ♪

03:16.935 --> 03:19.155
♪ Feel woozy from head to toe

03:19.199 --> 03:21.288
♪ Letting everyone know
I'm a rebel and a fighter ♪

03:21.331 --> 03:23.246
♪ This time,
I'm taking my time ♪

03:23.290 --> 03:25.814
♪ Taking my time,
taking my time, yeah ♪

03:25.857 --> 03:27.511
♪ So, hold on...

03:27.555 --> 03:30.427
[sighs]
You guys good?

03:30.471 --> 03:33.474
Uh, you-you...
you need anything, or...?

03:33.517 --> 03:34.997
GEORGE:
Unbelievable.

03:35.040 --> 03:37.217
NICK:
Yeah, I know, I know. Okay?

03:37.260 --> 03:38.566
I'll stop
being a helicopter.

03:38.609 --> 03:41.177
It's just, you know,
it's first-day nerves.

03:41.221 --> 03:43.919
No. No, not you. This.

03:44.963 --> 03:46.182
NICK:
Is that...?

03:46.226 --> 03:47.357
My biological father

03:47.401 --> 03:48.793
sending me a random
friend request?

03:48.837 --> 03:50.360
Yeah, it-it sure is.

03:50.404 --> 03:53.537
But you haven't spoken to him
in, what, 17 years?

03:53.581 --> 03:55.278
Yeah, which is why I
should probably expect

03:55.322 --> 03:57.193
a random friend request
from, what, Jesse's dad

03:57.237 --> 03:59.543
or-or Ted's next? I mean,
where does this madness end?

03:59.587 --> 04:01.328
Okay, okay.
You want to talk about it?

04:01.371 --> 04:02.720
I just did.[door opens]

04:02.764 --> 04:05.723
ACE:
My mom sends her regards.

04:05.767 --> 04:07.943
Where is everyone?
Did I get the date wrong?

04:07.986 --> 04:09.249
Thought today
was opening day.

04:09.292 --> 04:11.163
Oh, no. It is.

04:11.207 --> 04:13.601
Okay, snacks, right?

04:13.644 --> 04:16.473
You know, just in case.

04:16.517 --> 04:18.649
I mean, no pressure.

04:18.693 --> 04:21.652
♪ So, hold on

04:21.696 --> 04:24.351
♪ Things are moving

04:24.394 --> 04:25.961
♪ I know...

04:26.004 --> 04:27.484
These are solid.

04:27.528 --> 04:28.790
They're kosher, too.

04:28.833 --> 04:30.139
Ooh, it's time
to open up The Claw.

04:30.182 --> 04:32.707
You're driving. Come on.Okay.

04:32.750 --> 04:35.013
Hey.NICK:
Yeah.

04:35.057 --> 04:37.799
Congrats. This is great.

04:37.842 --> 04:39.975
Thank you. Thank you.

04:40.018 --> 04:43.631
See you.Happy opening day!

04:43.674 --> 04:45.502
Thanks.Uh, quick question.

04:45.546 --> 04:47.374
Have you considered
getting a bike rack out front?

04:47.417 --> 04:48.897
There's been a complaint

04:48.940 --> 04:50.638
from the owner of the
café across the street.

04:50.681 --> 04:53.031
Jake says he's losing business.Oh, wow.

04:53.075 --> 04:55.338
This place looks amazing.

04:55.382 --> 04:57.340
Thank you.Hi.

04:57.384 --> 05:00.038
Hi.What are you doing here?

05:00.082 --> 05:02.650
What am I doing? I'm
here to support Nick,

05:02.693 --> 05:03.868
hang out with you.

05:03.912 --> 05:06.088
You know, spend some
time with my daughter

05:06.131 --> 05:07.872
outside of the
house, right?

05:07.916 --> 05:09.874
At least until 2:00 p.m.

05:09.918 --> 05:11.876
That's specific.

05:11.920 --> 05:15.140
Oh, wow. Those
Ace's mom's cookies? Solid.

05:15.184 --> 05:17.839
What's up, you guys? Mmm.NICK:
Actually,

05:17.882 --> 05:19.275
I do need a little help
with their paperwork

05:19.319 --> 05:21.016
if you don't mind.No, not at all.

05:21.059 --> 05:22.844
I am in as long as
there's caffeine

05:22.887 --> 05:25.368
'cause I've been up
since yesterday.

05:25.412 --> 05:28.458
Hey, Nick?Yeah.

05:28.502 --> 05:32.157
Um, someone defaced the bathroom

05:32.201 --> 05:35.073
with some odd graffiti.

05:35.117 --> 05:37.641
Also, the lights
don't work.

05:37.685 --> 05:39.513
Oh.
Yeah.

05:39.556 --> 05:41.166
Okay.

05:41.210 --> 05:43.386
Well, I'll clean it up.

05:44.431 --> 05:45.693
And then I'll, uh,
have a talk with the kids

05:45.736 --> 05:48.043
about, uh, creative outlets,
right?

05:48.086 --> 05:50.567
Bet I can make it
a-a learning opportunity.

05:50.611 --> 05:53.353
Love it. Yes. Yeah.Right? Yeah.

05:53.396 --> 05:54.876
Oh.

05:54.919 --> 05:56.530
It's completely shameless.

05:56.573 --> 05:58.923
I don't know. I think Jake's
being a little sensitive.

05:58.967 --> 06:01.143
It's a public sidewalk.

06:01.186 --> 06:04.146
People can park their bikes.Hello? I meant this
friend request.

06:04.189 --> 06:05.495
I don't get it. Why now?

06:05.539 --> 06:07.584
This sperm donor has never tried

06:07.628 --> 06:09.891
to have a relationship
with me before.[Ace sighs]

06:09.934 --> 06:12.067
Is there any chance
that your dad found out

06:12.110 --> 06:13.634
about your upcoming nuptials?No.

06:13.677 --> 06:14.896
Victoria
would never tell him anything,

06:14.939 --> 06:17.594
and I haven't posted
anything online. I...

06:17.638 --> 06:20.423
Oh, the Fan Fan website.

06:20.467 --> 06:21.859
Ted.

06:21.903 --> 06:23.948
Ted blogged about the proposal.

06:23.992 --> 06:25.820
Is nothing sacred anymore?

06:26.864 --> 06:27.909
[groans]

06:28.953 --> 06:30.477
[sighs]

06:30.520 --> 06:32.087
[seat belt buckles]

06:32.130 --> 06:33.828
Ooh.

06:33.871 --> 06:36.134
Can I have one of these?
Sure could use a sugar hit.Oh.

06:36.178 --> 06:38.223
Oh, you know what? I was gonna
drop these off for someone.

06:38.267 --> 06:39.399
But...

06:39.442 --> 06:41.401
But what?

06:43.272 --> 06:45.230
But the chocolate melted.

06:45.274 --> 06:47.842
Yeah. It's gross. You
don't want to eat them.

06:47.885 --> 06:50.322
Get you a granola bar.

06:50.366 --> 06:51.889
[engine starts]Gross.

06:55.197 --> 06:56.677
JEAN:
We still don't know
anything more

06:56.720 --> 06:58.026
than what your client
has told us:

06:58.069 --> 07:00.594
that the tags are codes
for time and location

07:00.637 --> 07:02.160
of meeting place.

07:02.204 --> 07:05.207
Okay. And, um...

07:05.250 --> 07:07.383
You haven't been able
to figure out

07:07.427 --> 07:08.906
what the meetings are about?

07:08.950 --> 07:12.344
Uh, I mean, we think
it's drug deals.

07:12.388 --> 07:13.911
Now that your client
has gone AWOL

07:13.955 --> 07:16.566
after talks of
possible immunity...

07:16.610 --> 07:18.655
I've left Asher
a number of messages

07:18.699 --> 07:21.136
telling him how detrimental
his actions were.

07:21.179 --> 07:23.878
I haven't been able
to track him down. Yet.Well,

07:23.921 --> 07:25.314
I think we found
out where he was

07:25.357 --> 07:26.489
the night we were
supposed to meet.

07:26.533 --> 07:28.448
So, Asher was
caught on camera

07:28.491 --> 07:31.320
walking into an old cannery,
uh, two nights ago.

07:31.363 --> 07:34.497
Problem is he walked in,
but he never came out.

07:34.541 --> 07:36.368
Building's empty now.

07:41.461 --> 07:43.419
And this is the...

07:43.463 --> 07:44.986
security footage?Yeah.

07:45.029 --> 07:47.075
It's a-a five-block
radius of the cannery,

07:47.118 --> 07:49.033
uh, the night
he went missing.

07:49.077 --> 07:50.470
Okay.

07:51.558 --> 07:52.602
So, I've been meaning to scan

07:52.646 --> 07:54.169
through
all of this stuff myself,

07:54.212 --> 07:55.823
but now that I've been pulled
to the Trott case,

07:55.866 --> 07:59.827
I could really use
a second pair of eyes?Of course.

07:59.870 --> 08:01.350
I can take a look.

08:01.393 --> 08:03.395
Perfect.See if I spot

08:03.439 --> 08:05.572
any of Asher's
known associates.

08:09.837 --> 08:11.839
Amazing.

08:12.883 --> 08:15.451
[chuckles softly]Oh, my God.

08:16.452 --> 08:18.498
Thanks.Hmm.

08:24.808 --> 08:27.202
First the lights and now...

08:27.245 --> 08:29.247
♪

08:45.002 --> 08:47.004
♪

08:57.014 --> 09:00.148
[Trott's voice]: I'm a part
of something much bigger.

09:00.191 --> 09:02.846
You'll never understand.

09:02.890 --> 09:04.892
[panting]

09:14.989 --> 09:16.556
What the hell?

09:19.384 --> 09:21.386
♪

09:33.660 --> 09:36.619
What is your problem? You
just stole that woman's coffee

09:36.663 --> 09:37.751
and threw it at my head.

09:40.405 --> 09:43.757
Oh, no. I'm, um, I'm so sorry.

09:43.800 --> 09:45.367
I, uh, I don't know

09:45.410 --> 09:47.108
how I got here,
and I've been sleepwalking.Look,

09:47.151 --> 09:49.240
we all have crazy dreams,

09:49.284 --> 09:51.025
but you know
what we're not doing?

09:51.068 --> 09:53.505
Throwing beverages
at people, okay?

09:53.549 --> 09:55.725
Leave. Now.

09:55.769 --> 09:57.771
[whispers]:
Sorry.

10:00.817 --> 10:04.604
See? Better than drawing on
the bathroom wall, right?

10:04.647 --> 10:08.738
I just had my second nightmare
of the day.

10:08.782 --> 10:12.916
While seeing that exact image.

10:16.180 --> 10:17.747
First at the station,

10:17.791 --> 10:20.141
and then five minutes ago
at Jake's Café.

10:20.184 --> 10:21.664
I see it in my dreams, too.

10:21.708 --> 10:25.015
It's scary, but drawing
it makes me feel better.

10:25.059 --> 10:26.800
And...

10:26.843 --> 10:28.715
sorry about painting
your bathroom.

10:28.758 --> 10:31.892
Hey, it's all good.
Mistakes happen, huh?

10:34.068 --> 10:35.896
Hey, buddy.

10:35.939 --> 10:37.985
How long you been seeing

10:38.028 --> 10:39.900
that weird shape?

10:41.771 --> 10:43.033
Okay.

10:43.077 --> 10:44.426
It cannot be a coincidence

10:44.469 --> 10:46.863
that four people are
hallucinating the same thing.

10:46.907 --> 10:49.823
Yeah, in their dreams.
Uh, you know, I was thinking...

10:49.866 --> 10:52.173
We should call Hannah.
See if she knows anything.

10:52.216 --> 10:54.479
Hello? Uh, you know
I've been watching over

10:54.523 --> 10:55.959
the Historical Society
while Hannah is away.

10:56.003 --> 10:58.005
I can just dash over there
and find out everything I can

10:58.048 --> 10:59.746
about the silhouette
from your nightmares.

10:59.789 --> 11:01.443
You are welcome.

11:03.053 --> 11:05.055
[rock music playing softly
over speakers]

11:21.115 --> 11:23.247
[low snarling]

11:28.209 --> 11:30.254
[growls]

11:32.561 --> 11:33.954
[horn honks]

11:33.997 --> 11:35.782
Ace!

11:35.825 --> 11:38.219
What are you doing?

11:38.262 --> 11:40.221
[both panting]

11:40.264 --> 11:42.266
[phone chimes]

11:44.704 --> 11:46.357
What is this?

11:46.401 --> 11:49.578
That's something
I just hallucinated.

11:49.621 --> 11:50.753
[phone vibrates]

11:50.797 --> 11:52.015
NANCY:
Any guesses

11:52.059 --> 11:53.974
as to why I'm hallucinating
the same thing

11:54.017 --> 11:55.540
the Youth Center kids
are drawing?

11:55.584 --> 11:57.499
Well, it's the same thing
I just saw.

11:57.542 --> 11:59.196
Before he went
sleepwalking.

11:59.240 --> 12:00.894
RYAN:
Hey. Kwame

12:00.937 --> 12:03.026
and Talia just told me that they
started having nightmares

12:03.070 --> 12:05.115
about that thing three days ago.

12:05.159 --> 12:07.030
They-they keep calling it
the Sandman.

12:07.074 --> 12:09.424
Yeah, Bess said she
found something.

12:09.467 --> 12:11.295
She wants us to
meet up with her.

12:11.339 --> 12:15.430
Um, Ryan, can you hold down
the fort? Appreciate it.

12:15.473 --> 12:17.954
No, wait, I-I don't r...
Uh, any...

12:17.998 --> 12:19.608
[chuckles softly]

12:19.651 --> 12:22.742
Who wants more cookies?

12:22.785 --> 12:24.265
It's not just happening
to Ace and Nancy.

12:24.308 --> 12:26.049
Half dozen accounts are
tweeting about sleepwalking

12:26.093 --> 12:28.095
in Horseshoe Bay. Look.

12:28.138 --> 12:30.227
I recognize these names.

12:30.271 --> 12:32.752
Yeah, these guys
were a year below me and George.

12:32.795 --> 12:35.015
This girl was
in Ace's class, I think.

12:35.058 --> 12:37.800
Uh, so, the-the haunting
is escalating.

12:37.844 --> 12:40.020
It went from children's
nightmares to...

12:40.063 --> 12:42.022
To do what? Gain strength?

12:42.065 --> 12:44.764
When it's strong
enough, it...It jumps to teens.

12:44.807 --> 12:46.417
New food group.

12:46.461 --> 12:48.506
And now that it's stronger,
it's affecting them differently,

12:48.550 --> 12:51.074
making them sleepwalk.Into danger.

12:51.118 --> 12:53.294
Has anyone ever seen
the silhouette before?

12:53.337 --> 12:56.558
Yes. So, I have here...

12:56.601 --> 13:00.562
So, the Indigenous artisans
drew the image on pottery

13:00.605 --> 13:02.694
that they would then fill
with sand from Piper Beach.

13:02.738 --> 13:04.914
These-these pots
acted as dream catchers.

13:04.958 --> 13:08.483
Piper Beach? Like
we do every year

13:08.526 --> 13:11.094
at the town carnival?What's this got to do
with the town carnival?

13:11.138 --> 13:13.314
The carnival
has an opening ceremony

13:13.357 --> 13:16.056
where families go down
to Piper Beach and collect sand.GEORGE: Yeah.

13:16.099 --> 13:17.622
That you decorate
at the arts and crafts booth.

13:17.666 --> 13:19.233
You just make
little jars of sand.

13:19.276 --> 13:21.409
I used to dye my sand black.ACE:
Almost every kid

13:21.452 --> 13:23.803
in Horseshoe Bay
has one by their bed.

13:23.846 --> 13:26.283
Except for this year
because three days ago,

13:26.327 --> 13:29.112
Matthew Burke's corpse stopped
the carnival from opening.

13:29.156 --> 13:30.984
NICK:
Y'all have some crazy rituals.

13:31.027 --> 13:33.813
Well, just wait
till next month.What happens next month?

13:33.856 --> 13:35.075
You'll see.

13:35.118 --> 13:37.729
Hold on, when-when
did the town carnival start?

13:37.773 --> 13:39.949
1836.

13:41.908 --> 13:43.823
So, I think...

13:43.866 --> 13:45.650
Yeah, here. So,

13:45.694 --> 13:47.957
in the autumn of 1835,

13:48.001 --> 13:49.872
22 adults from Horseshoe Bay

13:49.916 --> 13:52.266
disappeared from their homes
in the middle of the night.

13:52.309 --> 13:55.269
And then most of their bodies
were found weeks later,

13:55.312 --> 13:56.661
washed up onshore.

13:56.705 --> 13:58.794
Old-timey sleepwalking
that led to the founding

13:58.838 --> 14:00.361
of the town carnival.NANCY:Okay.

14:00.404 --> 14:02.537
So, all we have to do is
get some sand from Piper Beach,

14:02.580 --> 14:04.191
make dream catchers,

14:04.234 --> 14:06.149
and then we can hand them out

14:06.193 --> 14:08.064
to the locals tomorrow morning.BESS:
I don't know.

14:08.108 --> 14:10.327
Three days ago
was a full moon,

14:10.371 --> 14:11.938
and we know that, uh,
the lunar cycle

14:11.981 --> 14:14.070
plays a huge role
in rituals, so...NANCY: Well,

14:14.114 --> 14:15.942
you might be right,
but are we supposed to wait

14:15.985 --> 14:17.508
until the next full moon
to find out?

14:17.552 --> 14:18.858
Because people
are sleepwalking,

14:18.901 --> 14:21.338
and somebody's gonna get
into some serious trouble

14:21.382 --> 14:23.601
if we don't
stop this now, so...

14:23.645 --> 14:25.038
I'm making the call.

14:25.081 --> 14:27.083
We're going to Piper Beach.

14:29.694 --> 14:31.305
Just...
[exhales]

14:35.091 --> 14:38.225
[faucet running, stops]

14:38.268 --> 14:39.313
CARSON:
Hey.

14:39.356 --> 14:41.750
You made primavera?

14:41.793 --> 14:43.230
I did.

14:43.273 --> 14:45.232
What was the occasion?

14:45.275 --> 14:47.712
No occasion. Just...

14:49.889 --> 14:52.413
Delicious.

