22:00.319 --> 22:02.364
George.

22:02.408 --> 22:03.800
Hey.

22:03.844 --> 22:05.628
...and how to stop it.NANCY:
Stay with me.

22:05.672 --> 22:08.718
Okay, we need to set alarms
on our phones to stay awake.

22:08.762 --> 22:11.634
And we should lock the doors
in case we do fall asleep.

22:11.678 --> 22:13.288
I can do you one better.

22:17.423 --> 22:19.947
Dad's a cop.

22:19.990 --> 22:22.341
Well, cool.

22:28.303 --> 22:30.261
NANCY:
What do we think

22:30.305 --> 22:33.134
is crucial about Piper Beach
with the dream catchers?

22:33.177 --> 22:35.005
[yawning]: I mean, there...
there appear to be

22:35.049 --> 22:36.833
a number of, uh, coastal tribes

22:36.877 --> 22:38.444
that dealt with sand rituals

22:38.487 --> 22:42.056
or-or stories about spirits
made out of particles of sand.

22:42.099 --> 22:43.579
I still feel
like we're missing something.

22:43.623 --> 22:46.626
What do you think, Ace?
[gasps]

22:49.977 --> 22:51.370
TROTT [whispering]:I'm part

22:51.413 --> 22:54.547
of something much bigger.

22:58.246 --> 23:00.683
I'm part
of something much bigger!

23:00.727 --> 23:02.032
[Nancy grunts]

23:04.252 --> 23:05.819
[grunts]

23:17.308 --> 23:19.398
[door opens]BESS:
Okay, just so you all know,

23:19.441 --> 23:20.703
