30:27.390 --> 30:29.392
[grunting]

30:30.393 --> 30:32.787
[women screaming]

30:36.225 --> 30:38.575
[thunder rumbles]

30:47.889 --> 30:50.109
[low growling]

30:53.634 --> 30:55.636
[Bess screams]

30:55.679 --> 30:56.942
ACE:Bess!

30:56.985 --> 30:59.553
Fix it, Dream Queen!

30:59.596 --> 31:01.816
Come on, Bess!Oh!Bess!

31:01.860 --> 31:03.731
[all grunting]

31:05.298 --> 31:06.560
GEORGE:
We're trapped!

31:06.603 --> 31:09.171
ACE: Come on, Bess!NANCY: You can do it, Bess!

31:09.215 --> 31:11.870
Come on, Bess!

31:17.049 --> 31:18.398
Come on, Bess!Come on, you can do it!

31:18.441 --> 31:20.443
You can do it!Come on, Bess!

31:20.487 --> 31:23.142
[exhales]

31:26.188 --> 31:28.190
Envision it.

31:30.018 --> 31:31.890
See it.

31:32.891 --> 31:35.763
Create it.[growls]

31:38.722 --> 31:40.246
Now!

31:42.117 --> 31:44.641
[loud crackling]

31:52.475 --> 31:55.914
♪

31:58.394 --> 32:00.527
[laughs]

32:00.570 --> 32:02.964
Yes, Bess!

32:03.008 --> 32:04.357
[gasps softly]

32:04.400 --> 32:06.750
Ow.
[groans]

32:09.753 --> 32:11.755
[exhales]

32:13.757 --> 32:15.585
[Bess grunts]NICK:
You okay?

32:23.419 --> 32:26.335
Does anybody remember
where we put the key?

32:31.819 --> 32:33.560
Hey, Bess, you have every
right to be angry with us.

32:33.603 --> 32:35.779
Okay, I'm not angry.

32:35.823 --> 32:39.958
I'm just disappointed and hurt.

32:40.001 --> 32:41.176
You deserve more
from your friends.

32:41.220 --> 32:43.309
Yeah, w-we should
have listened to you.

32:43.352 --> 32:44.571
Especially me.

32:44.614 --> 32:47.008
Hey, we're really sorry.

32:47.052 --> 32:49.054
Do you think you can forgive us?

32:49.097 --> 32:50.446
Oh, that depends.

32:50.490 --> 32:52.144
Are you all
gonna stop underestimating

32:52.187 --> 32:53.667
my knowledge of the occult
and supernatural

32:53.710 --> 32:55.756
and actually take my ideas
and opinions seriously?

32:55.799 --> 32:58.715
As much as anyone else's,
even Nancy's?

32:58.759 --> 33:00.761
Of course.100%.
I'll think about it.

33:00.804 --> 33:03.764
And respect my decision

33:03.807 --> 33:07.289
to assemble the next generation
of Women in White.

33:07.333 --> 33:10.292
I know in the past they stood
for some not-so-great things,

33:10.336 --> 33:12.120
but at their core,
the Women in White

33:12.164 --> 33:15.558
are about owning and-and
harnessing their power.

33:15.602 --> 33:17.734
That's what I believe
my calling is,

33:17.778 --> 33:20.215
and that's what
I intend to do.

33:20.259 --> 33:22.435
Then that is
what we will respect.

33:23.479 --> 33:25.090
I mean, I don't know. If she
starts wearing buckled shoes,

33:25.133 --> 33:26.265
I'm playing
the Pilgrim card.

33:26.308 --> 33:27.788
Oh, yada ya.Okay.

33:27.831 --> 33:29.268
[clears throat]

33:30.356 --> 33:33.402
You're gonna be
an amazing Woman in White.

33:34.447 --> 33:36.014
Thank you.[door opens]

33:36.057 --> 33:39.669
Hey. Nick, I, um, I
forgot to give this back to you.

33:39.713 --> 33:41.541
Why don't you
hang on to it.

33:41.584 --> 33:43.021
Kids said they
really liked you.

33:43.064 --> 33:44.631
They did?

33:44.674 --> 33:46.372
[chuckles]:
Why?

33:46.415 --> 33:48.504
Well, you were great with them.
Attentive,

33:48.548 --> 33:50.767
curious, uplifting.

33:50.811 --> 33:52.421
They're thinking of me
as a supervisor,

33:52.465 --> 33:54.206
but they see you as a peer.

33:54.249 --> 33:55.598
In a good way.

33:55.642 --> 33:57.644
You're from
a very different background,

33:57.687 --> 34:01.169
but you know what it's like
to not have a stable homelife.

34:01.213 --> 34:02.475
These kids could really benefit

34:02.518 --> 34:03.867
from spending some time
with you.

34:04.912 --> 34:06.696
Maybe

34:06.740 --> 34:08.785
that could go both ways?

34:11.397 --> 34:13.834
They-they really said
that they like me?

34:15.531 --> 34:19.187
I'll see you Monday, 9:00 a.m.

34:19.231 --> 34:21.668
Okay.

34:28.240 --> 34:29.937
Hey, Jesse.

34:29.980 --> 34:32.157
Thank you for taking Ted
to her trumpet lesson.

34:32.200 --> 34:33.767
Charlie
is still at her sleepover,

34:33.810 --> 34:35.595
but Emma's mom said she'll
bring her home after lunch.

34:35.638 --> 34:37.118
I told Nick
that I was running an errand,

34:37.162 --> 34:38.859
but it's something that I want
to deal with by myself,

34:38.902 --> 34:40.382
so it's your job
to sub in at The Claw.

34:40.426 --> 34:42.428
I'll explain later, okay?

34:43.864 --> 34:47.868
You got this. You got this.

34:49.739 --> 34:51.698
[exhales]

34:51.741 --> 34:54.309
[inhales sharply]

34:57.312 --> 34:59.706
All right, George.

34:59.749 --> 35:02.404
Come on, girl.
You got ten years left to live.

35:02.448 --> 35:04.885
It is time to face your demons.

35:11.892 --> 35:14.895
[footsteps approaching][exhales]

35:21.336 --> 35:24.296
Edwin George Chen.

35:24.339 --> 35:27.777
Can we talk
about this friend request?

35:33.174 --> 35:35.394
CARSON:
You want to tell me

35:35.437 --> 35:37.091
where you were all night?

35:37.135 --> 35:39.963
You want to tell me why the
primavera you made yesterday

35:40.007 --> 35:42.009
was missing your usual
measure of garlic?

35:45.621 --> 35:48.102
Garlic breath
isn't great for business.

35:48.146 --> 35:51.149
Are lunch dates with D.A.
Rosario good for business?

35:52.541 --> 35:54.891
I could smell her perfume.

35:54.935 --> 35:56.589
If you want to
date somebody,

35:56.632 --> 35:58.678
you don't have to
hide it from me.

35:58.721 --> 36:00.636
Not like you could, anyway.

36:01.681 --> 36:03.639
Just like I couldn't hide this
from you.

36:05.075 --> 36:07.774
I've been having
nightmares about Trott.

36:07.817 --> 36:10.429
He told me he's part of
something much bigger,

36:10.472 --> 36:12.953
something I would
never understand.

36:12.996 --> 36:16.870
So, I've been looking at these
articles going back to 2014.

36:16.913 --> 36:19.351
And I just--
I can't figure it out.

36:19.394 --> 36:20.830
What am I missing? Wh-Wh...

36:20.874 --> 36:23.093
What is he a part of
that I don't understand?

36:23.137 --> 36:24.573
Well...
[exhales]

36:24.617 --> 36:27.663
Why don't we start with
what you do understand.

36:27.707 --> 36:30.231
Okay. Um... I know he has

36:30.275 --> 36:31.493
three fingers on one hand

36:31.537 --> 36:33.016
because
of a self-inflicted accident.

36:33.060 --> 36:34.540
I know his license plate number.

36:34.583 --> 36:36.672
I know that he drives a van,

36:36.716 --> 36:38.805
which was probably used
to transport Dustin Yates' body

36:38.848 --> 36:40.198
from the kill site
to my car.

36:40.241 --> 36:41.721
Which wouldn't be
the first time

36:41.764 --> 36:44.550
that he used a van to dump
a victim's body. Look.

36:44.593 --> 36:47.770
His tire tracks were found at
every Frozen Heart crime scene.

36:47.814 --> 36:49.903
Except the town carnival.

36:52.993 --> 36:55.387
[screams]

36:55.430 --> 36:58.781
Trott couldn't have fit his van
into the corn maze.

36:58.825 --> 37:00.609
He would have had to carry
Matthew Burke's body

37:00.653 --> 37:03.090
into the maze.Which wouldn't fit
his "in and out" M.O.

37:03.133 --> 37:04.657
Plus, Matthew Burke's heart

37:04.700 --> 37:06.702
was completely removed
from his body,

37:06.746 --> 37:09.966
and Dustin's chest cavity
still had remnants of his heart.

37:10.010 --> 37:11.664
Two different M.O.s
could mean...

37:11.707 --> 37:13.274
Two different killers.

37:13.318 --> 37:14.797
[sighs]

37:14.841 --> 37:16.408
Trott said he was a part
of something much bigger

37:16.451 --> 37:17.626
because he's not the only killer

37:17.670 --> 37:19.715
in Horseshoe Bay.

37:19.759 --> 37:21.761
Be careful, please.

37:23.328 --> 37:25.068
Oh. Hello.ACE: Hey.

37:25.112 --> 37:26.679
Wh-What are you doing here?CARSON: Oh.

37:26.722 --> 37:28.333
I called him.

37:28.376 --> 37:31.161
Oh, okay. Bye.

37:31.205 --> 37:32.728
ACE:
Bye.

37:32.772 --> 37:35.427
♪ Can we wait...

37:35.470 --> 37:37.559
Should have this
depixelated and enhanced

37:37.603 --> 37:40.301
in about 43 seconds,
give or take.

37:40.345 --> 37:42.260
How are you not
a tech billionaire?

37:42.303 --> 37:44.653
Who says I'm not?

37:44.697 --> 37:46.742
♪ Finally...

37:46.786 --> 37:48.875
What exactly are
we looking for?

37:48.918 --> 37:52.052
Known associates of a
client of mine. D.A. thinks

37:52.095 --> 37:53.401
he got cold feet
and took off

37:53.445 --> 37:55.708
before she could get him
to turn state's evidence.

37:55.751 --> 37:58.276
He was last seen
walking into a cannery.

37:59.364 --> 38:02.889
The one on Harlowe Street?Yeah.

38:02.932 --> 38:03.933
Two nights ago.

38:03.977 --> 38:06.153
[computer trilling]

38:06.196 --> 38:09.548
Where's your client now?I wish I knew.

38:09.591 --> 38:12.333
Asher's never gone M.I.A.
this long with me before.

38:12.377 --> 38:14.030
I'm hoping
this surveillance footage

38:14.074 --> 38:15.684
explains his disappearance.

38:15.728 --> 38:18.339
I promised Jean I would take
a look, see if I can find

38:18.383 --> 38:20.341
any faces or cars
that might be able

38:20.385 --> 38:22.952
to point her
in the right...[computer chimes]

38:29.002 --> 38:30.960
I can explain.

38:31.004 --> 38:33.180
D.A. Rosario,

38:33.223 --> 38:35.530
Trott killed Dustin Yates

38:35.574 --> 38:38.141
but not Matthew Burke. There
has to be another killer.

38:38.185 --> 38:39.360
I know.
Trott has been in custody

38:39.404 --> 38:41.188
ever since he was arrested
in Portland.

38:41.231 --> 38:43.886
Another murder was just reported
with the same M.O.

38:43.930 --> 38:46.585
